===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*(s)neh₁-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|nedle}}, from {{inh|en|ang|nǣdl}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*nāþlu}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*nēþlō}}, from pre-Germanic {{m|gem-pro|*neh₁-tleh₂}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*(s)neh₁-|t=to spin, twist}}.

{{rel-top|Cognates}}
Cognate with {{cog|nl|naald|t=needle}}, {{cog|de|Nadel|t=needle, pin, crochet hook}}, {{cog|de|nähen|t=sew}}, {{cog|da|nål|t=needle}}, {{cog|no|nål|t=needle}}. Further related with Welsh {{m|cy|nyddu}}, Latin {{m|la|nēre}}, Sanskrit {{m|sa|स्नायति||wraps up, winds}}. Related to {{l|en|snood}}. {{rel-bottom}}

